1. Ukoliko ne uradite ono što vam je rečeno, susrešćete se sa *suprotnim* posledicama. (If you don't do what you were told, you will face *opposite* consequences.)
2. On je izneo mišljenje koje je u *suprotnosti* sa onim što smo se dogovorili. (He expressed an opinion that is *contrary* to what we agreed upon.)
3. *Suprotno* očekivanjima, taj projekat je bio izuzetno uspešan. ( *Contrary* to expectations, that project was extremely successful.)
4. Da li si siguran da ćeš otići u suprotnom smeru? (Are you sure you'll go in the *opposite* direction?)
5. Njih dvoje se uvek svađaju, jer imaju *suprotne* stavove. (They always argue because they have *opposing* views.)
6. Moj stav o toj temi je *suprotan* tvom. (My position on that topic is *contrary* to yours.)
7. Oni su međusobno *suprotstavljeni* i teško će se složiti oko bilo čega. (They are *opposed* to each other and it will be hard for them to agree on anything.)
8. Ponekad treba uraditi *suprotno* od onoga što se očekuje da biste postigli uspeh. (Sometimes you need to do the *opposite* of what's expected to achieve success.)
9. Ona je otišla u *suprotnom* pravcu i izgubila se u šumi. (She went in the *opposite* direction and got lost in the woods.)
10. Ova tvrdnja je u *suprotnosti* sa činjenicama. (This statement is *contrary* to the facts.)